<TITLE> Federation Cup postponed for a week </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 11 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) Monday postponed the ongoing Citycell Federation Cup for a week due to inclement weather as well as other national and religious occasions. The tournament will resume on Aug 18 on Monday's fixtures  Arambagh KS vs Sunrise SC and Dhaka Mohammedan SC vs Rahmatganj MFS. "The federation postponed the tournament for seven days following the inclement weather, national mourning day and Shab-e-Barat," said Fazlur Rahman Babul, chairman of the fixture and bylaws committee of the BFF. The final round of the Federation Cup got underway on Aug 6 and a total of 10 matches had been held before the weather intervened. To reduce the pressure on the Bangabandhu National Stadium, the BFF considers taking six to seven Federation Cup matches outside the capital to Gazipur, which earlier hosted the qualification round matches. In this regard, the BFF will sit with the officials of the participating teams, said Babul. The federation also considers holding the Federation Cup's semifinals and final after the Eid-ul-Fitr and starts B. League after the completion of the Federation Cup quarterfinals. 
